        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The axle stop bolts and nuts must be replaced with new bolts and nuts when performing this
                        Service Procedure.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>The axle stop (Figure 1) can be lowered one bolt hole by placing a bolt through the upper hole of the
                axle stop and the lower hole in the frame rail. A new lower hole will need to be drilled in the frame.
                Use the axle stop as a template for marking the position of the new bolt hole (Figure 2). The new hole
                should be located directly below the upper hole for proper orientation of the axle stop. Tighten the
                mounting bolts to 195 to 240 Lbf-ft (265 to 325 Nm). Once this modification has been made, the ride
                height should be set using TSI-04-03-01. Refer to the dimension for chassis built on or after 2/23/04.
            </para>
